 I'm assuming you're asking for the second cited reference in the text. However, without the full text, I cannot directly access the reference number 2. Here's a general example of how to format a citation for a journal article:

{
  "Citation": {
    "Authors": ["Last name, Initial.", "Last name, Initial.",...],
    "Year": ["Year of publication"],
    "Title": ["Title of article"],
    "Journal": ["Title of Journal"],
    "Volume": ["Volume number"],
    "Issue": ["Issue number"],
    "Pages": ["Starting page number-Ending page number"]
  }
}

